race.comment: SISTINE CHAPEL (11) doesn't boast the best strike rate but has hit the top-four in all seven starts this preparation and it's hard to knock mares in form. Gets in well at the weights with the claim and looks well-placed against this line-up. Will prove tough to hold out. CHAYSE 'N' LEISA (3) broke the maiden status over this track and trip last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that victory. Can go right on with the job now. BLINDING SPEED (9) boasts a win around this circuit and gets 3kg weight relief. Top-three candidate. MARATHIA (6) is a last-start winner who cannot be discounted lightly.
